A second body has been recovered in Coffee Bay in the Eastern Cape following devastating floods in the area. For more, eNCA speaks to Zimkhita Macingwane, head of communications at the OR Tambo District Municipality. #DStv403 COFFEE BAY - The bodies of two children who were swept away during floods in Coffee Bay in the Eastern Cape have been recovered. The body of a 4-year-old, who is the sister of the 6-year-old who was recovered on Sunday morning, was found. READ:Â Eastern Cape Floods | Coffee Bay residents seek flood relief At least four other people are still missing. Residents of the Wild Coast town are some of the worst affected by the floods that wreaked havoc across large parts of the province.